{
  "text": "Adiponectin is one of the adipocytokines secreted by adipocytes. In addition, it has also been revealed that hypoadiponectemia is closely linked with insulin resistance along with hyperinsulinemia [CITATION_1] . Various studies have demonstrated anti-atherogenic and antidiabetic properties of adiponectin [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . In a previous study, green tea polyphenol (EGCG) significantly increased the level of adiponectin concentration in rats, which act as biomarker in obesity and its related complications [CITATION_4] . A weight loss study revealed that adiponectin level was decreased in obesity, whereas increased with weight loss [CITATION_5] . Similar effects have also been observed in the present study, whereby treatment of polyphenolic rich EECCL increases concentration of plasma adiponectin by 45.03 and 41.58% in both low and high dose treated groups compared to that of HFD. The significant increase of adiponectin concentration was in accordance with the decrease in visceral fat mass, body weight gain and plasma insulin concentrations. The results were in accordance with that of previous studies, which suggested that increase in adiponectin level is associated with weight loss [CITATION_6] .",
  "correct_citation": {
